div.h2: Step-by-step hypothesis evolution with beam pruning

g.text: Step 3: Final beam with completed hypotheses

pre.code:
for h in beam.get_active(): if h.is_complete: beam.completed.append(h) continue
logits = model(h.sequence) log_probs = F.log_softmax(logits[-1]) top_k = torch.topk(log_probs, beam_width)
for token, lp in zip(top_k.indices, top_k.values): new_h = h.update(token, lp.item()) if token == EOS_ID: new_h.is_complete = True all_candidates.append(new_h)
# Prune to beam_width best all_candidates.sort(reverse=True) beam.hypotheses = all_candidates[:beam_width]
return beam
